snippet: The girls’ swim team at Carmel High School, from a northern suburb of Indianapolis, won nine of 12 events at the state finals to cruise to a 30th consecutive state title.
abstract: Carmel High School girls' swim team in Indiana wins 30th consecutive state title, breaking 30-year-old record for longest title streak by high school team in any sport.
lead_paragraph: The girls’ swim team at Carmel High School, from a northern suburb of Indianapolis, won nine of 12 events at the state finals to cruise to a 30th consecutive state title.
